AI-POWERED CHATBOT USING MERN STACK AND GEMINI API
1. PROJECT OVERVIEW

--->Project Title:
AI-Powered Chatbot Integration into MERN Application using Gemini API

--->Objective:
To design and integrate an AI chatbot into a MERN stack web application that uses Google Gemini API for intelligent conversation handling, real-time streaming, and secure user interaction.

--->Goal:
Build a complete full-stack application capable of real-time AI communication with persistent conversation history, authentication, and context management.

2. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Traditional chatbots often rely on predefined responses, lacking adaptability and real-time intelligence.
The challenge is to create a dynamic chatbot that:
⦁	Connects to Gemini API for advanced AI interactions.
⦁	Maintains session context and memory per user.
⦁	Provides streamed responses for a natural chat flow.
⦁	Persists all data in a MongoDB database securely.

3. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE

The project follows a MERN architecture:

⦁	MongoDB: Stores user sessions, chat history, and metadata.
⦁	Express (Node.js): Acts as a backend server and API layer connecting React and Gemini API.
⦁	React: Provides the interactive front-end chat
⦁	Node.js: Handles server-side operations, authentication, and message routing.
⦁	Communication between React frontend and Node backend happens via REST APIs and SSE (Server-Sent Events) for real-time token streaming.

