7. CSS & FRONTEND DESIGN OVERVIEW

⦁	ELEMENT: Chat Container (Main UI Box)
⦁	background-color: #ffffff; — clean chat box appearance
⦁	border-radius: 10px; — smooth curved edges
⦁	box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); — raised effect
⦁	ELEMENT: Message Bubbles
⦁	User messages: light blue (#d0e7ff)
⦁	Bot messages: light gray (#f1f1f1)
⦁	padding: 10px; and margin: 5px; for spacing
⦁	ELEMENT: Input Field
⦁	Full-width input box with rounded corners
⦁	border: 1px solid #ccc; for separation
⦁	padding: 12px; font-size: 16px; for usability
⦁	ELEMENT: Send Button
⦁	background-color: #4a90e2; color: white; — visually prominent
⦁	border-radius: 5px; — consistent design
⦁	cursor: pointer; — clear interactivity

8. WORKFLOW

⦁	User opens the React chat interface.
⦁	Sends a mssage → React sends it to backend /chat endpoint.
⦁	Node.js Express server processes and forwards it to Gemini API.
⦁	Gemini API responds with tokens (streamed in real time).
⦁	Backend streams response using SSE/WebSocket to frontend.
⦁	MongoDB saves full conversation and session details.
⦁	User can clear chat, summarize context, or continue chatting.

9. RESULTS

⦁	Successfully implemented real-time streaming chat with Gemini API.
⦁	Achieved secure JWT-based authentication.
⦁	Persistent session memory and summarization working correctly.
⦁	Optimized token usage and latency performance.
⦁	Developed a clean, responsive React UI for chat interactions.

